$$
f(x) = \begin{cases}
\dfrac{a}{b}x & \text{if } x \le -4 \\
abx^2 & \text{otherwise}
\end{cases}
$$

where $a > 0$ and $b > 0$. If $f(-4) = -\dfrac{60}{13}$ and $f(4) = 3120$, find the sum of $a$ and $b$. The final answer is 28.
